data.title: Chisapani, Khotang
data.text:
Chisapani is a town and Village Development Committee in Khotang District in the Sagarmatha Zone of eastern Nepal. At the time of the 1991 Nepal census it had a population of 4,276 persons living in 791 individual households.[1]

References

^ "Nepal Census 2001". Nepal's Village Development Committees. Digital Himalaya. http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1 .

Chisapani High School in Khotang district was established in 2028 bs. Ishwor Adhikari, who is the second student to pass in first division in the history of the school is now works in Chicago, US. He is trying to approach school officials to contribute some assisitants to bright but financially needy students of the school.
